The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Pak spy 

 New Delhi, Sept. 21: Delhi police have arrested a Pakistani and his accomplice here on espionage charges and have recovered 17 photographs and maps of sensitive defence installations in Gangtok, reports our correspondent.

 Delhi police?s special cell arrested Asif Raees alias Nadeem Ahmed alias Kabir Malhotra last night and his cousin Naushad Ali for helping him stay illegally in India. Asif was arrested from a cybercafe in Yamuna Vihar, deputy commissioner of police (special cell) Ashok Chand said. 

 He said Asif had been trained in espionage by Pakistan Army intelligence. 




